  "title": "Head of Junior Development & Programs",
  "description": "<p><strong>Summary:</strong><br />We are seeking a full-time Golf Professional to lead the development of our junior academy and school programs. This role involves creating training curriculums, managing junior and school events, and maintaining a full teaching schedule.</p><p></p><p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><p><ul><li>Develop and implement junior and school golf programs.</li><li>Organize events, training camps, and competitions to promote golf development.</li><li>Deliver high-quality coaching sessions to aspiring young players.</li><li>Work with schools and partners to integrate golf into educational curriculums.</li><li>Track student progress and ensure structured development pathways.</li><li>Organizing academy events.</li><li>Active in academies marketing strategies.</li></ul></p><p><strong>Required Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum Class “A” status in a major Professional Golfers' Association.</li><li>Minimum Bachelor’s degree and above</li><li>At least 3 years of experience teaching junior/school golf in an international setting.</li><li>Proven experience in developing junior golf programs and working with internal / external stakeholders</li></ul>",
